#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.165"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.165:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.165:0.2"
msgid "17. Āghātavagga"
msgstr "17. Resentment"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.165:0.3"
msgid "165. Pañhapucchāsutta"
msgstr "165. Asking Questions"

# See my note on the similar idiom at AN 4.170. Here, as there, these cases are incompatible, so to say “for five reasons or one of them” doesn’t make sense.
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.192"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.165:1.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi … pe … “yo hi koci, āvuso, paraṃ "
"pañhaṃ pucchati, sabbo so pañcahi ṭhānehi, etesaṃ vā aññatarena."
msgstr ""
"There Venerable Sāriputta addressed the mendicants: … “Whoever asks a "
"question of another, does so for one or other of these five reasons."

msgctxt "an5.165:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi?"
msgstr "What five?"

#. VAR: momūhattā → momuhattā (bj)
#. VAR: atha vā panevaṃcitto → atha vā pakuppanto (si, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.165:1.3"
msgid ""
"Mandattā momūhattā paraṃ pañhaṃ pucchati, pāpiccho icchāpakato paraṃ pañhaṃ "
"pucchati, paribhavaṃ paraṃ pañhaṃ pucchati, aññātukāmo paraṃ pañhaṃ "
"pucchati, atha vā panevaṃcitto paraṃ pañhaṃ pucchati:"
msgstr ""
"Someone asks a question of another from stupidity and folly. Or they ask "
"from wicked desires, being naturally full of desires. Or they ask in order "
"to disparage. Or they ask wanting to understand. Or they ask with the "
"thought,"

#. VAR: ce → no ca (s1-3)
msgctxt "an5.165:1.4"
msgid ""
"‘sace me pañhaṃ puṭṭho sammadeva byākarissati iccetaṃ kusalaṃ, no ce me "
"pañhaṃ puṭṭho sammadeva byākarissati ahamassa sammadeva byākarissāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If they correctly answer the question I ask it’s good. If not, I’ll "
"correctly answer it for them.’"

msgctxt "an5.165:1.5"
msgid ""
"Yo hi koci, āvuso, paraṃ pañhaṃ pucchati, sabbo so imehi pañcahi ṭhānehi, "
"etesaṃ vā aññatarena."
msgstr ""
"Whoever asks a question of another, does so for one or other of these five "
"reasons."

msgctxt "an5.165:1.6"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho panāvuso, evaṃcitto paraṃ pañhaṃ pucchāmi:"
msgstr "As for myself, I ask with the thought,"

msgctxt "an5.165:1.7"
msgid ""
"‘sace me pañhaṃ puṭṭho sammadeva byākarissati iccetaṃ kusalaṃ, no ce me "
"pañhaṃ puṭṭho sammadeva byākarissati, ahamassa sammadeva byākarissāmī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If they correctly answer the question I ask it’s good. If not, I’ll "
"correctly answer it for them.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.165:1.8"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
